## Output argument with multiprocess
Using multiprocess and colorama will cause output(`print`) argument, which won't appear without colorama.

I've tried adding a process lock, which seemed that didn't function.
BTW, without colorama, process lock is not needed.
But I didn't use any shared variables...
So I guess the argument happened when outputting...

I've also searched for some information about process lock **during outputting**, but I couldn't find any.


