Suppose I have the following IAM policy on an SQS Queue:

```JSON
{
  "Id": "arn:aws:sqs:us-east-1:12345:queue-name/SQSDefaultPolicy", 
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Action": [
        "SQS:SendMessage"
      ],
      "Condition": {
        "ArnEquals": {
          "aws:SourceArn": "arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:12345:sns-topic"
        }
      },
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "*"
      },
      "Resource": "arn:aws:sqs:us-east-1:12345:queue-name",
      "Sid": "Sid12345"
    }
  ] , 
  "Version":  "2012-10-17"
```

This is what you get if you use the AWS GUI to subscribe an SQS queue to an SNS topic.

The policy clearly restricts SendMessage to just that single SNS topic, yet it still triggers the "SendMessage authorized to all principals" error.

