The convert_choice_name function in converters.py forces all string choices to upper case. These are the values taken from the choices field of a Django model field. This is a very bad idea because:

- It forces the developer to use upper case in GraphQL methods, even if lower or mixed case is used everywhere else in Django apps.
- If makes all choices case silently insensitive. This silently imposes a constraint that Django does not impose, introducing very difficult-to-detect bugs.

graphene_django should (must) respect the developers' decisions on the case of choice elements, rather than force upper case. The fix is to replace:

    def convert_choice_name(name):
        name = to_const(force_text(name))
        try:
            assert_valid_name(name)
        except AssertionError:
            name = "A_%s" % name
        return name

with:

    def convert_choice_name(name):
        name = force_text(name)
        try:
            assert_valid_name(name)
        except AssertionError:
            name = "A_%s" % name
        return name

